"title": "5849: exaltation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5849: exaltation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The lifting up or raising on high of a person, in words or actions. The exaltation of Jesus Christ, first on the cross and then in his resurrection, provides a model of how God exalts the humble and obedient. God also humbles those who exalt themselves. Believers are called upon to exalt God in their praise of him.</p>\n<h2>True exaltation comes from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:6-Ps75:7\">PSA 75:6–75:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:1-Gen39:6\">GEN 39:1–39:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:1-1Sam2:10\">1SA 2:1–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:18-2Sam7:29\">2SA 7:18–7:29</a></p>\n<h3>God exalts those who are humble</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:10\">JAS 4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:3-Matt5:5\">MAT 5:3–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:46-Luke1:55\">LUK 1:46–1:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5-1Pet5:6\">1PE 5:5–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of God's exaltation of his people</h2>\n<h3>God's exaltation of Joshua</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:7\">JOS 3:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God's exaltation of David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:9-2Sam5:12\">2SA 5:9–5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:47-2Sam22:51\">2SA 22:47–22:51</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:46-Ps18:50\">PSA 18:46–18:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:19-Ps89:29\">PSA 89:19–89:29</a></p>\n<h3>God's exaltation of Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:25\">1CH 29:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:5-1Kgs3:15\">1KI 3:5–3:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:7-2Chr1:12\">2CH 1:7–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:1-1Kgs10:10\">1KI 10:1–10:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:1-2Chr9:9\">2CH 9:1–9:9</a></p>\n<h2>God's exaltation of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Prophecies of Jesus Christ's exaltation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:13\">ISA 52:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1-Ps110:7\">PSA 110:1–110:7</a></p>\n<h3>The exaltation of Jesus Christ upon the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:14-John3:15\">JHN 3:14–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:32\">JHN 12:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a></p>\n<h3>God's exaltation of Jesus Christ in the resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:32-Acts2:36\">ACT 2:32–2:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30-Acts5:31\">ACT 5:30–5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></p>\n<h2>Self-exaltation is wrong</h2>\n<h3>Warnings against self-exaltation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:6-Prov25:7\">PRO 25:6–25:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:19-Dan4:27\">DAN 4:19–4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:5-Matt23:12\">MAT 23:5–23:12</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:38-Mark12:39\">MRK 12:38–12:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:45-Luke20:47\">LUK 20:45–20:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:7-Luke14:11\">LUK 14:7–14:11</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of self-exaltation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:13-Isa14:14\">ISA 14:13–14:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:3-Gen11:4\">GEN 11:3–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:1-Ezek28:2\">EZK 28:1–28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:1-Dan3:7\">DAN 3:1–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:3-2Thess2:4\">2TH 2:3–2:4</a></p>\n<h3>Consequences of self-exaltation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:12\">MAT 23:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:11\">LUK 14:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:5-Gen11:9\">GEN 11:5–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:11-Isa2:17\">ISA 2:11–2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:12-Isa14:20\">ISA 14:12–14:20</a> <em>taunt against the king of Babylon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:28-Dan4:33\">DAN 4:28–4:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>\n<h2>The exaltation of God in his people's praise</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1-Exod15:2\">EXO 15:1–15:2</a></strong> <em>Rejoicing after the exodus from Egypt.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:1-Ps34:3\">PSA 34:1–34:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:9-Ps57:11\">PSA 57:9–57:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:5\">PSA 99:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:1-Ps145:13\">PSA 145:1–145:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:1\">ISA 25:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:36-Dan4:37\">DAN 4:36–4:37</a></p>",
